}{\f1 \fs20 \b \cf1 *1621}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1  D. Second Opinions and Committee Input}\par 
\pard \qj \fi0 \li0 \ri0 {\f1 \fs20 \cf1 {\pard \par }
  Another possible method to mitigate the influence of cognitive bias on prosecutorial decision making is to involve additional, unbiased decision makers in the process. The reduction of bias might be achieved internally within a prosecutor's office by establishing a process for "fresh looks" of a }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzSDUNumber35}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzSDUNumber35}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 file by a lawyer or a committee of lawyers whose evaluation would not be tainted by earlier developments in the case. }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzFN_B188}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzFN_B188}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }{\field {\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK \\l Document1zzFN_F188 }}{\fldrslt {\f1 \fs20 \ul \cf2 [FN188]}}}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1  For example, such a process might be helpful when the prosecuting attorney learns of a new piece of potentially exonerating evidence and the initial theory of guilt might cause her to undervalue its importance. }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzFN_B189}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzFN_B189}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }{\field {\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK \\l Document1zzFN_F189 }}{\fldrslt {\f1 \fs20 \ul \cf2 [FN189]}}}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1  A fresh look might also be helpful when the credibility of a piece of evidence that contributed to the prosecutor's initial charging decision is undermined. A separate attorney would be able to comment on the strength of existing evidence against the defendant without the taint of a preexisting theory of guilt. }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzFN_B190}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzFN_B190}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }{\field {\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK \\l Document1zzFN_F190 }}{\fldrslt {\f1 \fs20 \ul \cf2 [FN190]}}}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1  Similarly, a fresh look attorney would not be biased by the desire to avoid the cognitive dissonance associated with having charged an innocent person with a crime. }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzFN_B191}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzFN_B191}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }{\field {\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK \\l Document1zzFN_F191 }}{\fldrslt {\f1 \fs20 \ul \cf2 [FN191]}}}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }\par 
\pard \qj \fi0 \li0 \ri0 {\f1 \fs20 \cf1 {\pard \par }
  Limitations exist, however, in another prosecutor's ability to provide a neutral evaluation of a coworker's case. Herbert Packer observed long ago the operational "presumption of guilt" that allows the fast-paced case screening process in most district attorneys' offices to function. }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzFN_B192}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzFN_B192}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }{\field {\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK \\l Document1zzFN_F192 }}{\fldrslt {\f1 \fs20 \ul \cf2 [FN192]}}}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1  At least some prosecutors might open each }{\f1 \fs20 \b \cf1 *1622}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1  new file assuming that police would not have arrested the suspect and referred him for charges if they did not have their man. }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzFN_B193}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzFN_B193}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }{\field {\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK \\l Document1zzFN_F193 }}{\fldrslt {\f1 \fs20 \ul \cf2 [FN193]}}}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1  Accordingly, a prosecutor serving as a fresh look attorney may be tainted by an initial theory of guilt even before reading a police report. Moreover, a fresh look attorney may be reluctant to dissent from }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzSDUNumber36}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzSDUNumber36}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 her colleague's initial case evaluation. The social science literature demonstrates the difficulty decision makers have in resisting the power of their peers. }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzFN_B194}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzFN_B194}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }{\field {\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK \\l Document1zzFN_F194 }}{\fldrslt {\f1 \fs20 \ul \cf2 [FN194]}}}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1  For example, in Solomon Asch's classic studies on conformity, he found that large percentages of subjects could be induced to reach erroneous conclusions in a simple line-matching task if a number of the researchers' confederates first answered incorrectly. }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzFN_B195}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzFN_B195}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }{\field {\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK \\l Document1zzFN_F195 }}{\fldrslt {\f1 \fs20 \ul \cf2 [FN195]}}}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }\par 
\pard \qj \fi0 \li0 \ri0 {\f1 \fs20 \cf1 {\pard \par }
  Accordingly, a more meaningful fresh look process might involve an advisory committee that includes nonprosecutors. Asch's research on conformity demonstrated the power of even one lone dissenting voice to encourage people to depart from group opinion and assess a problem independently. }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzFN_B196}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzFN_B196}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }{\field {\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK \\l Document1zzFN_F196 }}{\fldrslt {\f1 \fs20 \ul \cf2 [FN196]}}}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1  Judges, defense attorneys, and civil practitioners would be less likely to apply a presumption of guilt and would feel less pressure to conform their views to other prosecutors; accordingly, they may be more likely to provide a true fresh look. }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzFN_B197}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzFN_B197}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }{\field {\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK \\l Document1zzFN_F197 }}{\fldrslt {\f1 \fs20 \ul \cf2 [FN197]}}}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }\par 
\pard \qj \fi0 \li0 \ri0 {\f1 \fs20 \cf1 {\pard \par }
  }{\f1 \fs20 \b \cf1 *1623}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1  Some prosecutors might resist the involvement of outsiders in the case-evaluation process as an unwarranted intrusion into prosecutorial discretion. However, the full scope of prosecutorial discretion could be preserved if the fresh look committee served solely in an advisory capacity and the district attorney's office retained ultimate decision-making authority. Moreover, the committee's advisory capacity could be limited to specific questions, such as the strength of a case or the potential value of exonerating }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzSDUNumber37}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzSDUNumber37}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 evidence. }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzFN_B198}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzFN_B198}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }{\field {\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK \\l Document1zzFN_F198 }}{\fldrslt {\f1 \fs20 \ul \cf2 [FN198]}}}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1  Such a limited consulting role would not involve the committee in the broader policy questions that generally justify deference to prosecutorial discretion, such as the jurisdiction's enforcement priorities or where a single case fits within those priorities. }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzFN_B199}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzFN_B199}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }{\field {\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK \\l Document1zzFN_F199 }}{\fldrslt {\f1 \fs20 \ul \cf2 [FN199]}}}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }\par 
